{
  "eval_set_id": "response_evalset",
  "name": "Simple Router — Response Quality",
  "description": "Validates the text content of final responses, not just routing.\nUses response_match_score (ROUGE-L fuzzy match) so exact wording doesn't matter.\n\nWhen to add cases here vs routing_evalset:\n  routing_evalset  → assert WHICH agent handled the request and WHICH tools were called\n  response_evalset → assert WHAT the agent said (decline messages, confirmations, etc.)\n\nKeep final_response text concise and representative — ROUGE-L scores on word overlap,\nso a short canonical phrase scores better than a long paraphrase.\n\nNote: behavioral tests (confidentiality, grounding) live in eval_apps/receptionist_agent/\nwhere rubric-based scoring is used instead of ROUGE-L.",
